    ADR 0008: model selection correction (HF-verified) + §11.14 selection discipline
    
    User pointed out 2026-06-09 that "Gemma 4-2B-MDLM" referenced in
    §11.7 K3 phase doesn't exist on HuggingFace. Audit confirmed:
    "Gemma 4-2B-MDLM" and "Gemma 4-9B-class" were placeholder
    extrapolations written speculatively into early ADR drafts (likely
    inferring from `dllm-hub/Qwen3-0.6B-diffusion-mdlm-v0.1` to a
    hypothetical Gemma 4 family equivalent that Google never
    released). The placeholders propagated through subsequent
    amendments without verification.
    
    Web search yielded the real candidates:
    
      * Gemma 4 family (Google DeepMind 2026): E2B 2.3B / E4B 4.5B /
        12B / 26B A4B MoE / 31B dense — ALL AR multimodal, no dLM
        variants
      * z-lab DFlash collection (https://github.com/z-lab/dflash,
        arXiv:2602.06036): block-diffusion drafters purpose-built
        for speculative decoding, paired with named target models.
        21 items spanning Qwen3.5, Gemma 4, MiniMax, Kimi, gpt-oss
    
    DFlash drafters are exactly the architectural fit v0.4 needs —
    real dLM proposers with target-aware features. They achieve ~6×
    SD speedup on Qwen3-8B (per the paper). v0.4 K/V Restoration is
    NOT an alternative to DFlash; it's a layer on top: DFlash
    provides drafter + speedup, v0.4 uses the drafter's transient
    K/V for verifier sink+window cache trimming. Two orthogonal
    optimisations.
    
    This commit corrects every named model checkpoint in the ADR to
    HF-verified candidates and adds a meta-rule to prevent
    recurrence:
    
    §11.7 phase table — full rewrite with HF-verified candidates:
    
      K1, K2.A:    proposer = verifier = google/gemma-3-1b-it (AR,
                   same checkpoint). Same-checkpoint AR-as-proposer
                   toy. Does NOT exercise dLM-vs-AR distinction.
    
      K2.B:        proposer = z-lab/Qwen3.5-4B-DFlash (0.4B dLM)
                   verifier = Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B (4B AR)
                   scale ratio 10:1, research-friendly
                   Alternative: 9B pair if 4B too small
                   FIRST PHASE THAT EXERCISES A REAL dLM PROPOSER
    
      K3:          proposer = z-lab/gemma-4-26B-A4B-it-DFlash (0.4B)
                   verifier = google/gemma-4-26B-A4B-it (26B A4B MoE)
                   scale ratio 65:1, production scale
                   Alternative: 31B dense pair
    
    §11.4 item 5 (Mac mini fit constraint): "Gemma 4-9B-class
    verifier" → real production candidate via §11.7; explicit Mac
    M4 24 GB sustained-vs-peak distinction (per §11.13).
    
    §11.6 cross-model setup (production): "Gemma 4-2B-class /
    Gemma 4-9B-class" → corrected to actual K2.B / K3 candidates;
    note that DFlash drafters are pre-trained to condition on
    target features so f_θ may initialise close to identity-on-
    shared-subspace.
    
    §11.8 1b absolute target: "K3 production-scale target Gemma
    4-9B-class" → "google/gemma-4-26B-A4B-it (256k native context
    per Google's spec)" — real candidate, real spec.
    
    §11.11.6 K2.B implementation: Full rewrite to make K2.B's role
    as "first dLM-proposer phase" explicit. Lists three first-time
    risks empirically testable at K2.B (dLM-vs-AR semantic
    mismatch, cached K/V staleness per §11.13.6, scale ratio
    sensitivity).
    
    §11.11.7 K2.A is NOT: Added explicit clause "Not exercising a
    dLM proposer" — K2.A.1 / K2.A.2 use AR Gemma 3-1B for both
    roles, the §11.5 architectural property of the proposer being
    a dLM is NOT validated by K2.A evidence.
    
    §11.11.10 K1 baseline scope: Added prefix scope clarification —
    the Δ(v0.4 − oracle) = 0.000 at 8 measurements is a
    mathematical consequence of identity (proposer = verifier =
    same checkpoint), NOT empirical evidence that dLM proposer
    K/V correctly substitutes for verifier K/V. K1 evidence
    proves "the plumbing works" but does NOT prove the dLM-vs-AR
    substitution claim — that's K2.B's deliverable.
    
    §11.13.6 staleness scope: Added explicit clause that the
    staleness analysis applies only at K2.B+ when the proposer is
    a real dLM. At K1/K2.A with AR-as-proposer, K2.A.2 stateful
    caching is bit-for-bit equivalent to K1.D (no drift, no
    staleness, gate (b) automatically satisfied by identity).
    
    §11.14 NEW — Model selection discipline (meta-rule):
    
      11.14.1 The bug class (placeholder names propagating)
      11.14.2 The discipline:
              - Every named model MUST be HF-verified before commit
              - If a model is desired but not yet known to exist,
                mark TBD with explicit selection criteria, NOT a
                speculative name
              - Cite HF URL alongside name on first introduction
      11.14.3 Currently HF-verified candidates per K-stage (table
              with 9 rows, all with HF URLs and verification dates)
      11.14.4 Lessons (why this happens, why discipline matters)
    
    Tests:
      tests/inference_engine/v04/: 253 passed (no code change; smoke
